--- Ted Kitch <tedkitch(-at-)tedsgarage.com> wrote:
>My 76 isn't idling like she should be.  She has a 2L FI (GD code) engine.
>I've checked the dwell (48) and the timing is right on the money at 7.5 BTDC
>and doesn't fluctuate at all.  I checked all of the valves and they are at
>.006.  I also checked my compression and I have 1-123 2-122 3-121 4-123.
>The spark plugs look fine.  With the dwell meter hooked up and the engine
>warm the idle fluctuates from 780 to 950.  Turning the idle adjustment screw
>will raise the numbers, but the fluctuation is the same.  I've looked
>through my Bentley and there are multiple causes, but I thought that I would
>ask the list to narrow it down before I begin testing everything on my
>engine.
